service notes: Title: 2022 Hyundai Tucson - Camshaft Position Sensor Replacement

Issue:
- Check Engine Light illuminated
- Extended cranking/hard starting condition
- DTC P0342 (Camshaft Position Sensor 'A' Circuit Low Input)

Diagnostic Steps:
1. Retrieved and confirmed DTC P0342
2. Performed visual inspection of sensor and associated wiring
3. Conducted circuit testing which revealed erratic signal voltage
4. Confirmed Camshaft Position Sensor failure

Repair Procedure:
1. Identified correct replacement part (OE/Bosch P/N 393183C100)
2. Replaced Camshaft Position Sensor following proper installation procedure
3. Applied manufacturer-specified torque specifications
4. Cleared diagnostic trouble codes
5. Performed verification testing

Results:
- Check Engine Light extinguished
- Normal cranking and starting operation restored
- Engine operating within normal parameters
- All systems verified functioning properly

Technical Notes:
- Always use OE or high-quality replacement sensors
- Proper torque specification is critical for sensor operation
- Complete circuit testing is essential for accurate diagnosis
- Post-repair verification should include cold start testing 
